values:
i can't believe it has been so long since i posted. mainly b/c i know i have only a few readers here... anyways, today is the last day i will don VT gear as my "black veil" - don't get me wrong, i will still continue to wear Hokie pride - but i've decided today is the last day i'll do it in memoriam. i am tired. i am tired of crying, tired of talking, tired of being in a holding pattern. i am gathering what strength i have and moving forward. still affected but headed with a bit of forward motion. this is something that i think my head/heart/soul will always carry but... i must not stay in this swirling pattern of grief. i need to find the ground again. 

i'm not sure if that makes me human, inhuman, indifferent. but i barely know how to grieve and i've been doing it for days now.

Music meme game

if you're up for playing, this game is fun...

1. Put your playlist on shuffle.
2. Post the first lines to the first 25 songs to come up (along with these instructions).
3. Have people guess the songs and artists in comments to the post.
4. A couple of days later, post the answers to the ones people guessed correctly. Post the first two lines of the ones no one got and get people to guess again.
5. Repeat, adding the next line to the unguessed songs each time, until they're all guessed/you've posted the whole song/you've gotten bored/no one's going to get the damn thing if you don't tell them.

The list:
1. Its hard to argue when you won't stop making sense
2. The devil's in the dreamin'

4. I know what you want
5. How do I get through one night without you

instead of flying off the handle!

13. I heard there was a secret chord
14. Its like any other day, Rose
15. Time is never time at all

18. There were some scientists

25. She wanted to be a cowboy, she was shooting 'em down

I'm leaving for Denver tonight. And do you know what that means?!?! That means I'll be in Norfolk, VIRGINIA (how exciting!) tomorrow by dinner time. I've missed the east coast... and I so look forward to seeing my illdrawnbalcony Yay!

I'm going to have the hottest date in town! ;-)

*squeels with glee!*

so lately i've been just kinda making a mini list in my head of songs that i need to try and acquire. this list is definitely eclectic and a bit on the bizarre side... but... yeah... i'm writing it here to help commit it to memory.

black velvet - alannah myles
safety dance - men without hats
rock me amadeus (i blame you illdrawnbalcony for not owning it yet ;-P) 
Respect - aretha franklin 
moon river (from breakfast at tiffany's) 
as time goes by (from casablanca) 

i'm sure there's more and i'll add accordingly. but these are the ones i just happened to think of.

heehee. we were discussing 80's country songs today... and someone brought up the Statler Brothers. This made me laugh muchly. (being from the same town as them) and how my grandmother had the door opened for her by one of them. She was so pleased that day. It made me smile thinking about that and her.

an additional thought of the day: 

my friend very embarrassingly admitted last night that she watches PBS documentaries. and i didn't see how that would be embarrassing, since another group of my friends and i got together this past summer on several occassions to watch a documentary series on PBS (so in a sense, we had viewing parties) and my ex and i used to check out documentaries from the library. 

i won the dorky contest. again.

first off, its snowing again. ITS MAY, GOD, NO MORE SNOW IN MAY! WINTER ENDS IN MARCH/APRIL! ugh. 

i'm sitting around, dancing to "Tangled in Blue" - the Indigo Girls cover of this song. I need to see some good concerts. At least Louisville has a pseudo-music scene. I have seen that both Girlyman and Dar Williams have played there. Maybe inspiration for some of you to visit me??

the song of the weekend: mr. jones ~counting crows

came up at random times, random places all weekend long 

matched my mood... 
my feelings of inadequacys...

"...She's suddenly beautiful
We all want something beautiful
I wish I was beautiful..." 

"...when everybody loves you, you can never be lonely..."

MULTIPLY IT BY 20!!!!!!!!!!!!! 

it was so pretty saturday. the remanants of that 2 foot blizzard was gone. and i wake up this morning (monday) and there's another 8 inches of snow on the ground. ugh. i'm so sick of winter. thinking happy warm things, thinking happy warm thoughts.
i'm sick of snow. this two feet better be it till next winter. rawr. or else!

so i got a coloring book in the mail from one friend on monday morning. 

i received a fabulous set of crayons from another early last month. 

can i mention how cathartic coloring was?!?! :) i felt like a child. it was great.

those who know me well know that i've been thinking through and figuring out a "crush"

what have i discovered about myself? i don't want a boyfriend. i'm not ready. i've got too much to work through. i don't want to throw my feelings towards others in that manner. and that makes me feel more liberated than i have in a while. i sincerely apologize for all the trouble i've caused.

that's all.

so, i keep running across this story and someone at the AP definitely must have been giggling when they mentioned the fact that the engineer continuously blew the horn. its just messed up. but i giggle and almost feel guilty for doing it. but... i think maybe in my mind its like hearing people SCREAMING at deaf people thinking they will eventually hear them? the story just reeks of that kind of ignorance.

i'm so nervous about everything, i think i'm going to throw up. 

ugh.

sorry i'm not updating as much. its been a crazy busy time!!!! 

i've got vagina monologues today and tomorrow! yes, i'm performing a monologue (and a shorter piece) 

and then friday, i leave for 4 days for an alternative spring break trip! 

i'll be back tuesday/wednesday of next week with bells on :-)

oh Rent, how you just seem to pertain. i like this song, just for the fact that it reflects the fears of everyone. and to be able to echo them in a safe group is moving. 

so here is the thoughts in my head.. (and i like the fact my sister and i are common souls in this sense, and both cry everytime we hear it)

Will I? 

Will I lose my dignity?
Will someone care?
Will I wake tomorrow 
from this nightmare?

i'm oddly enough craving to reread "a midsummer's night dream" and "hamlet" 

and recently, i've watched a few movies with ralph fiennes in... and i am finding him intriguingly hot.

i think all this goes well with my new draw to the british?!?! i feel like a turncoat ;-P

so, i just saw casablanca for the first time back in november and i'm already in the mood to watch it again. 

i'm addicted.

i'm thinking about another year of AmeriCorps in South Dakota. even though i've complained about this state non-stop the past year. 

Advantages: 
~watch this program to advance
~be more comfortable with this town and with the people in it
~i really like my little attic apt
~i usually like my location the second year (second year of college, second year of grad school)
~it would be an extension of experiences i need, including more grantwriting! which would get me hired in the non-profit sector.
~Spearfish has taught me to simplify my life 
~i wouldn't be paying moving costs
~it has taught me to be very independent and self sufficient
~i'm more likely to stay single.


Disadvantages
~its far away from EVERYBODY i know. 
~the job isn't perfectly in my field (i'm more into international issues, its a very homogenous town - its also higher ed focused and i'm not) 
~there is no long term prospects and i'm only procrastinating
~it has made me more of a loner
~i'm more likely to stay single

should i watch the opening ceremonies of the winter olympics tonight? or should i watch either gilmore girls or whatever movie i have in the house (knowing that all of them are good :-P)


cuz i definitely need to not go out. its way freezing and i'm way exhausted and need more sleep than i got yesterday (this winter and 8 hours of sleep are not very friendly towards each other)

call me crazy.

so those who know me, know i'm in a geographic debate... where do i go to find my next AmeriCorps position/non-profit job. (i'm not limited to AmeriCorps positions, but there would be advantages...) but in the midst of a geographic dillema. and today, the weirdest thing happened. i heard a city's name. and the thing is, it has sounded more perfect (at least for now) than any other city i could possibly think of. REALLY weird. everywhere i have thought of has drawbacks. so there seems to be a list of 3 unlikely cities that i'm seriously considering. (that i have no job prospects for, mind you all! before any excitement comes) what's even weirder, is each one of them has a weird family quest association to them. so that just makes me wonder...

anyways, the city that had the really freakish/nonlogical/heart lead/god lead (whatever you want to call it) was: baltimore, md and yes , oddly enough when you mentioned it, the epiphany was the most peaceful one i've had about ANY city that anyone mentioned. and i have NO clue why. so, i'm gonna be looking into it. i'm not sure about permanency or anything. but something still makes baltimore sound/feel more right than any other city.

other two cities: phoenix, AZ and charleston, SC (or columbia, SC - meh close enough)

granted, my most logical searches are: seattle, wash DC, boston, nyc (so i know the difference and won't dismiss them, but may spend a little time researching these options most. - and most heavily. (for now.)

just weird, thought i'd share. i still have a furrowed brow... its been a bit since the conversation and yeah, i'm still thrown off.

just cuz its fun.

hot fudge yesterday, cashmere today? geez i keep upping the self-nurturing ante...
